y orbit. The available X-ray data\nprovide additional evidence for the existence of the colliding stellar winds in\nthe system. Another possible source of the polarized light could be scattering\nfrom the stellar photospheres. The models with circumstellar envelopes, or\nmatter confined to the orbital plane, do not provide good constraints on the\nlow inclination, better than i < 27 deg, as is already suggested by the absence\nof eclipses.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 1 Jun 2016 09:58:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-06-02"}
